						<!-- /post-title -->

	<!-- post-meta -->
	<p class="post-meta"> 
					<time datetime="2013-02-25" class="post-date" pubdate>Feb 25, 2013</time>
		
						<span class="post-author"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/author/cloder/" title="Posts by Courtney Loder" rel="author">Courtney Loder</a></span>
				<span class="post-category"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/category/research/design-by-youth/" title="View all posts in Design by Youth" rel="category tag">Design by Youth</a>, <a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/category/research/knowledge-infrastructures/" title="View all posts in Knowledge Infrastructures" rel="category tag">Knowledge Infrastructures</a></span>
										    
	</p>
	<!-- /post-meta -->
	
	
<!-- post-image -->
<!-- /post-image -->

<!-- post-content -->

	<p>The research project Knowledge Infrastructure Policy: From Shrinking Cities to Sustainable Cities revolves around a STEM collaboration with teenaged students from Orange County high schools. Bringing together STEM learning and participatory design, the project has a sharp focus on the reclamation of urban space as a community activity. The goal is not only to learn how(&#8230;)</p>

