						<!-- /post-title -->

	<!-- post-meta -->
	<p class="post-meta"> 
					<time datetime="2013-01-13" class="post-date" pubdate>Jan 13, 2013</time>
		
						<span class="post-author"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/author/cloder/" title="Posts by Courtney Loder" rel="author">Courtney Loder</a></span>
				<span class="post-category"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/category/research/" title="View all posts in Research" rel="category tag">Research</a></span>
										    
	</p>
	<!-- /post-meta -->
	
	
<!-- post-image -->
				<figure class="post-image ">
							<a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/values-in-design/"><img src='http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/themes/suco/themify/img.php?src=http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/VIDWorkshop_txt.jpg&amp;w=670&amp;h=' alt='Values in Design'   width='670'  /></a>
					</figure>
			<!-- /post-image -->

<!-- post-content -->

	<p>We host an annual workshop which brings together graduate students and faculty from a wide-ranging array of fields with the purpose of creating a shared theoretical basis and practice for values-centered design.The Values in Design Doctoral Workshop is a week-long, intensive event sponsored by the Values in Design Program through the Department of Informatics in(&#8230;)</p>

